data.title: A twist on sushi
data.text: Let the client select the location and the food was great.  Mid lunch hour and a bit of a crowd out front = it must be good.  Not much of a wait...and quick seating.  Waitress knew the menu well and made us some appetizer recommendations...sashimi and a twist on edamame.  Right choice!!  A few rolls came out with a unique serving platter and deliciousness was served.  Return trip is on the schedule...just to try another taste from the diverse menu!!

data.title: FUN place to enjoy dinner
data.text: This is a fun place to go, servers are attentive and food is great.  The best place to sit is at the bar.  You can watch the chiefs prepare all those yummy dishes.

data.title: Lunch Sushi
data.text: Bomb-diggity. If you like sushi, you will like this classy sushi hot spot in the middle of downtown modesto. Food was great. Service was great. Presentation as good as I have seen.  The place is a little pricey. The temperature was colder than most restaurants and made my wife uncomfortable. Bring a sweater. I will return.

data.title: Good sushi
data.text: Fun atmosphere, lively, good bar.  Sushi is good, not amazing.  Innovative rolls, good selection.  Priced a little high.

data.title: Best sushi in town.  Love it!!!
data.text: If you are looking for great food and nice place in Modesto, then this is it.  The 'Dante inferno' was amazing.  Not as spicy as the name implies, but still delicious.

data.title: Excellent service.  The  garlic edamame is to die for!!!
data.text: We had Excellent service, food, cocktails :-)  Restaurant is clean, great bar.  Overall service is friendly, I recommend it highly.  I can't wait to go back.  I have gone for lunch as well as dinner.  A great place to go for a special event.  The garlic edamame is by far my favorite item on the menu.

data.title: Bliss
data.text: Best sushi I've ever eaten! What an amazing evening we had for my husbands birthday.  Truly amazing sushi. The sushi chef's were top-notch as well as staff. The fresh scallop roll was excellent,  but my favorite roll was the chef's choice. Thank you for making my palate rejoice.

data.title: Elegant sushi restaurant
data.text:
What an unusually elegant sushi restaurant Raw is! It has a strikingly modern vibe, with a stunning bar area where one may enjoy drinks and sushi as they watch the sushi chefs and mixologists perform their craft. The restaurant also has an area set apart, where one may have a private party.  Quite a few  bistro tables and chairs are on the sidewalk in front of the restaurant.

On the spur-of-the-moment on a Saturday night we decided to have dinner at Raw.  We waited about half an hour before finally seating at the bar.  We found it odd and confusing to see two spaces marked reserved at the bar,so we thought the bar area was also by reservation. The hostess initially tried to seat us at a table for two set up in the private room which was already occupied by a party of about 20, but we refused.  The service was a little spotty. The first waitress didn't introduce herself nor state if she was going to take our drink and food order or only one and which one.  We ended up ordering with the sushi chef, and a waiter and waitress walking around. The friendly sushi chef was the most helpful.

data.title: Sushi at it's finest.
data.text:
Based on a recommendation from a business we visited this location for a late afternoon snack and a glass of wine.  Long story short, this was one of my better choices for a recent business dinner while in the Modesto Ca. area.  From Melinda at the bar  -  Management  -  and fantastic Sushi, this is the local restaurant to visit for a great evening of food, drink and sociability.
WT Cote

data.title: GREAT menu!
data.text: I love the huge selection of rolls offered on their menu.  They are huge, so watch out and don't order too much at first.  Sample and order more if you are still hungry.

data.title: One of the Very Best
data.text: I grew up in San Francisco, so I am a bit of a "fish snob" in restaurants. I have eaten sushi all over the place and, believe it or not, this is one of the finest I have ever had. Everything is spectacular... I especially like the sesame tuna appetizer, the Dante roll, and the Neff roll... but I like spicy. They have something for just about every taste. The wine, the staff, and the service is outstanding as well.

data.title: Dinner before Gallo event
data.text: In close proximity to the Gallo Center for the Arts, a very convenient and good location for dinner. Reservations strongly recommended. Very popular. Full bar. Lengthy menu of a wide variety of sushi dishes. Very helpful waitperson to help novices. Plenty of tasty food at reasonable prices.

data.title: Sushi could have been cooked more!
data.text:
We picked this restaurant from the Trip Advisor restaurant ratings for Modesto. The name suggests the speciality is sushi and it was. We were looking for a light dinner and with the menu being very comprehensive, there was lots of choices and a change to reorder if we wished. 
We also picked this place based on it's proximity to our hotel. Don't you hate it when you are in a new place at night and nothing seems familiar. You just want to get to your hotel rather than tour the city!
Strangely enough this restaurant was right down town. We expected traffic/ parking issues. Neither was the case as we ended up parking the car three doors down from this restaurant and it took us 10 minutes to get there. You can't beat that!
We ordered a draft beer (double IPA) which had great flavor and was cold to suit the warm temps here in Modesto.
I have difficulty remembering what we  ordered  but one of the orders was rainbow roll. I ordered a roll of something and a soba soup. Everything was excellent and we were full. Good portions and fresh. The soba soup should have lots of fish in it but it was still good with the large noodles that I like. When I left some soup in the dish, I asked the waiter to put it is in doggy bag. Before telling her that I was kidding, she was willing to do so. We all laughed.
The only criticism I had was that the waiter was a little too much in a hurry to serve us. This is a personal assessment but it was a feeling.
The restaurant had padded seats around the edges of the restaurant with a private venue for the more romantic(?) The other tables had 2 or more seats.  The music was probably ok for the people that were there but as more people arrive the overall noise level could be a factor for some. We usually like a quieter time to be able to talk between us without raising our voices. 
The evening went well as we left with a full stomach and a happy heart.

data.title: Impressive
data.text: The sushi was great.  Offerings included the standards but also some unique combinations.  Chicken teriyaki was very good as well.  The atmosphere is wonderful, high ceilings and bar top as well as standard height tables, cool lighting, very modern.  Super clean as well.  Service was a little slow but certainly friendly.  We had five in our party and did order several types of sushi, the chicken teriyaki and some tempura appetizers.  Sushi rolls were larger than what we typically get at restaurants in our area with at least 8 large pieces per roll.  Full service bar available.

data.title: Date night
data.text: We visited here on a Friday night for our anniversary. Great ambiance, very friendly and attentive service, nice selection of food and drink choices, and we received our order very quickly. Their sushi rolls are fairly large and plated beautifully. Our only disappointment was when we tried to order dessert and learned they don't serve any dessert on the weekends. We enjoyed our dinner and drinks, but we ended up going doing the street for dessert and to finish out our evening.

data.title: Outstanding Food and Service
data.text: They are just down the street from the Gallo Arts Center, so were very convenient to go to eat after the show.  The food was delicious and the service was outstanding.  We'll be back for sure.

data.title: Great Sushi Downtown Modesto
data.text: Nigiri sake (salmon) excellently done, and fresh! Garlic edamame was a pleasant surprise. Staff was friendly, and efficient.

data.title: Great Sushi
data.text: Great downtown location, the menu has a variety of items to choose from. The atmosphere is contemporary, the resturant and bar area is well appointed. The staff is friendly a familiar with the beverage and food menus.

data.title: Best Sushi in Modesto!
data.text: Love the Sushi at Raw Sushi Bistro!  The restaurant gets packed so I suggest reservations.  Everything is amazing!  I especially enjoy the Spicy Sesame Tuna Appetizer, it's seared tuna that is served with chili oil in a ponzu sauce...so delicious!  The specialty rolls are HUGE!  Enough for three people! The presentation is beautiful too!  The Sashimi is of the highest quality, exceptionally fresh and tasty. They have a great drink selection too and a good size bar area.  The ambience, service, food, everything is excellent here...can't wait to go back!  They also have live music most weekends.

data.title: Birthday Celebration
data.text:
Awesome place! Excellent service! Super delicious sushi! 
This was my first time eating at this restaurant. I must say that I was totally impressed. If you love sushi, this is an excellent restaurant.
